    <sys:String x:Key="Text_PrivacyPolicy">Privacy Policy</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Text_PrivacyP1">PocketDrop is a free, open-source app provided "as is", without any express or implied warranty. The author is not liable for any damages arising from the use of this software.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Text_PrivacyP2">PocketDrop does not collect, store, or share your personal information or data. The app accesses certain local data - including files and folders on your device, clipboard contents, and basic device information - solely to provide its core functionality. This data never leaves your device and is not transmitted to, collected by, or shared with any third parties. The only routine network activity the app performs is a standard ping to GitHub to check for new version releases.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Text_PrivacyP3">PocketDrop collects anonymous crash and hang reports to improve app stability. This data is non-identifiable and contains no personal information, and is never shared with third parties.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Text_PrivacyP4">This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. You are advised to review this page periodically for any changes.</sys:String>
